mortar.dagger1support

Interface Blueprint

  • Deprecated. 
    see deprecation note on ObjectGraphService.requireChild(MortarScope, Blueprint)

    @Deprecated
public interface Blueprint
    Defines a scope to be built via ObjectGraphService.requireChild(MortarScope, Blueprint) or ObjectGraphService.requireActivityScope(MortarScope, Blueprint).

    • Method Summary

    • Method Detail

      • getMortarScopeName

        String getMortarScopeName()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the name of the new scope. This can be used later to find it in its parent. If ObjectGraphService.requireChild(MortarScope, Blueprint) is called again with a Blueprint of the same name, the original instance will be returned unless it has been MortarScope.destroy() destroyed}.

      • getDaggerModule

        Object getDaggerModule()
        Deprecated. 
        Returns the @Module that will define the scope of the new graph by being added to that of its parent. If the returned value is an instance of Collection its contents will be used as modules. Returns null if this scope needs no modules.
        See Also:
        ObjectGraph.plus(Object...)
